<p>When evaluating potential construction companies in Chicago, always check for proper licensing, insurance, and a strong portfolio of completed projects. Ask for references and read online reviews. A reputable contractor will be transparent about their pricing, provide a detailed contract, and communicate proactively.<br/>Avoid companies that demand large upfront payments without a clear scope of work or offer suspiciously low bids, as these often signal hidden costs or subpar quality. For specific services like <a href="/services#drywall">drywall installation</a> or custom carpentry, inquire about their specialized experience and craftsmanship.</p>

